<div id="outline-container-sec-3" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="sec-3"><span class="section-number-2">3</span> Government Expenditure and Revenue Scotland (GERS)</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-3">
<p>
The <a href="http://www.gov.scot/Topics/Statistics/Browse/Economy/GERS">Government Expenditure and Revenue Scotland</a> figures are made up of estimates based
on assumptions that are open to interpretation and debate. It is however, the nearest
thing we have to 'official' figures!
</p>

<p>
So lets leave the debate on how 'accurate' the numbers are, and get on and use them!
</p>
</div>
</div>

